p &nbsp 0<br>wis&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 0<br>mana&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 0<br><br>The special field allows you to specify a value to the effect on the item. For instance, the beastlords set the special to 200 on a fungi, due to the effect &quot;Fungal Regrowth&quot;.<br><br>Based on the above weightings, I plugged in each of the helms from RadBarsh's Updated Armor Comparison Chart, and the helms were ranked in the following order:<br><br>Warlord<br>Myrmidon<br>Raldukan<br>Champion<br>Fierce Her<br>Berserker<br>Fine Her<br>Cobalt<br>Moktor<br>Indicolite<br>Crustacean<br>Soldier's<br>Crafted<br>Ry'gorr<br><br>You can view the whole thing at <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.enter.net/~jon/helms.htm">www.enter.net/~jon/helms.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>So why am I here? I'd really like to make this tool available to all of my fellow warriors, but it needs to be right. I'm asking for your feedback on the weighting stats, so that items are ranked as they should be. I also know that because of the AC softcap, HP would be worth more once you exceed that cap. I'm not sure how to work that into the equation.<br><br>On a side note, if this has already been done, stop me now and hook me up with a link. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uvaraho1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Varaho1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 825<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/28/02 8:06:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4032.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Feedback Wanted: Stat Weighting</span><hr size=1> AC ( up to 1300 on your toon. There is some AC formula out there ) &gt; HP <br><br>6 hp = 1 sta<br><br>sta&gt;agl&gt;dex&gt;str 'till you get 200 ( remember you have starting stats )<br><br>Saves are all worth the same but less than everything else. ( untill stats and AC cap that is )<br><br>Remember this is baced on what is now, Pop will raise the stat caps and do who knows what other nasty things. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uvaraho1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Varaho1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0> at: 9/28/02 8:14:21 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uxorizjebekis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xoriz Jebekis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/28/02 4:59:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4032.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Feedback Wanted: Stat Weighting</span><hr size=1> This is what I use (yes, really)...<br><br>AC = 100<br>HP = 1000<br>STR = 5<br>STA = 6000<br>AGI = 25<br>DEX = 25<br>MR = 9<br>DR = 10<br>PR = 10<br>FR = 10<br>CR = 10 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uthorilan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>thorilan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 216<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/29/02 6:34:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4032.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left cl